title: For Sale:  Sig Sauer P938 Equinox with goodies
postcontent:
This is the Sig P938 (9mm) Equinox with some goodies to make it a super deal for someone looking for a small carry 9mm pistol. SIG SAUER now offers the ballistic advantage of the 9mm cartridge in a platform similar in size to the best-selling P238 pistol. A single-action-only trigger, coupled with full-size SIGLITE® Night Sights makes the P938 handle like a much larger pistol, yet is still easy to carry concealed. A polished Nitron two-tone slide is paired with a black hard coat anodized frame. Tru-Glo® front and SIGLITE rear sights. I have less than 200 rounds through this gun.....hardly used!

With dimensions just slightly larger than its .380ACP counterpart, the P938 packs six plus one rounds of
9mm into an all-metal frame. The cocked-and-locked single-action trigger gives the P938 unmatched
accuracy in a pistol its size.

Fans of the 1911 will find the thumb safety, magazine release and slide stop lever in familiar places. An
ambidextrous safety makes the P938 easy for left- and right.

The pistol comes with one 6 round mag but I am including another 6 round and a 7 round mag. I have two extra holsters besides the plastic one that comes with base gun. A Remora tuck and a leather pocket holster which prevents it from printing. Using the leather wallet holster makes it appear as a wallet in your front or rear pocket. The Remora stays put in your waistband or pocket due to the outside material keeping it in place while pulling gun out of it....very nice.

I also installed the Tillamook Precision stainless steel trigger....much easier on your finger but makes for a nice crisp trigger....much improved over the stock plastic.

I am also including a Hogue grip which makes a very nice 'purchase' when pistol is in your hand. The Hogue is larger than the stock grips and allows you to get a fuller grip and with the 7 round mag the pinky extender allows for a much improved grip for larger hands.

I would like to sell as complete package and looking to get $738 cash.

Must have ID plus PTC or PTP to purchase. Receipt signed by both parties.

title: For Sale:  TRD "The Real Deal" HEAVY Black Leather Motorcycle Biker Jacket
location: West Side, Cleveland, OH, Cleveland, Ohio
postcontent:
This is a high quality, custom built, heavy-duty black leather motorcycle jacket made by The Real Deal in Cleveland, Ohio, a leather boutique specializing in motorcycle leather. 

http://www.trdleather.com  

Features

- Extremely rugged, full grain, THICK leather.  This jacket weighs 10 lbs.  I ordered it extra heavy duty, and got it. Their standard thickness leather jacket is made from 1.3-1.4mm cowhide -- I don't have calipers to measure with, so I'm not sure HOW thicker this is, but it is seriously thick.
- Removable liner.
- Two inside pockets, large enough to hold a compact semi-auto if you CCW.
- Four external pockets: 2 hand warmer pockets, a diagonal chest pocket, and a small front pocket.
- Epaulets.
- Lace-up sides.
- Attached belt.
- Brass hardware.  All zippers are heavy-duty brass YKK zippers.  (The lining zipper is silver colored, but all external hardware is brass.)

Fit and Story

This was a custom order jacket, and I could not return it.  Overall I am VERY happy with the jacket... except for the fit. I am 5'10" 180 lbs, 42" chest and 36" waist, and they fitted me wrong, and I waited too long to exchange it.  

The story goes like this:  I purchased my first TRD jacket at the Cleveland Motorcycle Show in 2004, in size 42.  It fit like it was made for me from day one, extremely comfortable, and I wore that jacket almost daily for six years, and in that time it was just starting to get nicely broken in.  In the winter 2010 it was stolen. Remembering the label, I could only remember the letters TRD, so I tried looking up on the internet and found that they were a local outfit with a good reputation for building quality jackets.  

So I went and bought this one that I'm selling today, brand new as a custom order in spring 2011.  Between 2004 and 2010, I had gone from 140 lbs to about 160, so the 42 had been fitting a bit snug, and I wanted to go up to a 44.  They measured me and advised to go a size larger so I could layer under it in cold weather, so I ordered a 46.  I had wanted some custom features which deviated from their standard 2010 design, to keep as close to my old jacket as possible. They built it for me, I tried it on, it seemed to fit well enough, I took it home.

In late Spring, before I had a chance to wear it on its inaugural ride, I broke my arm in a bicycle accident, and could not wear it again until I recovered from my injuries.  That winter, following my recovery, I put it on and went to my garage and sat on the bike, to find that it fits a bit too long for me in the torso.  When seated in a riding position, my thighs push the waist of the jacket up, causing the entire jacket to shift up.  In the summer this would let in a lot of wind and be a nice feature, but for colder weather it would be too much.

So if you are about 5'10" and have a 30" inseam like I do, then for your torso length this is probably not a good jacket for you.  However,  If you are  6'0" - 6'2" and 200-210 lbs, with a 44-46" chest and about a 36-38" waist, it would probably fit you very well.  

Measurements

Size: 46 (according to tag)
Sleeve length: 26" (measured from where the sleeve joins the shoulder to cuff.)
                       33" (measured from where the collar meets the shoulder to cuff.)
Body length: 28" (measured from center of base of collar to bottom hem of rear of jacket.)
Chest width: 25" (measured armpit to armpit across the back.)

If you need any other measurements, please ask!!

Price, Terms, Conditions

Condition is offered as "New Without Tags" because the jacket never had tags on it.  It is essentially new, has just been hanging in the closet for about 2 years.

I am trying to represent this jacket as completely and honestly as I can.  No returns are offered, so if you have any questions about measurements please ask.  If the listing is active, it's still available.  Serious inquiries only, please.

title: For Sale/Trade:  38 CAL .357 Magnum XTP (100 Rounds)
location: NW OKC, Edmond, Oklahoma City, Oklahoma
postcontent: This ammo is almost impossible to find pre-loaded right now. XTP pistol bullets continue to set the standard as the bullet of choice for hunters and law enforcement officers who understand the value of a pistol bullet which will perform over a wide range of handgun velocities. Most pistol bullets are designed to work only at a factory specified velocity and a specific range. At these predetermined specifications, the bullets work just fine. But when bullet velocity begins to change, surprises can happen. Many factors cause velocities to change-gun type, barrel length, distance to target, barriers and more. That's why you need a bullet that you can depend on to perform over a wide range of velocities. You need the XTP.
